              "point": "～ば～ほど",
              "meaning": "\"This pattern expresses a proportional relationship: \"\"The more [A], the more [B].\"\" It repeats the verb or adjective twice—first in the conditional 'ba' form, then in the dictionary form followed by 'hodo'.\"",
              "sentences": "年を取れ<b>ば</b>取る<b>ほど</b>、考え方が固くなる。<br>(The older you get, the more rigid your way of thinking becomes.)<br><br>運動すれ<b>ば</b>する<b>ほど</b>、体力がつく。<br>(The more you exercise, the more stamina you gain.)<br><br>そのアイドルが人気であれ<b>ば</b>人気である<b>ほど</b>、チケットが取れない。<br>(The more popular that idol is, the harder it is to get tickets.)<br><br>今が幸せであれ<b>ば</b>ある<b>ほど</b>、なくなるのが怖い。<br>(The happier I am now, the more I fear losing it.)"
