              "point": "まるで～のようだ",
              "meaning": "\"This structure creates a strong simile, meaning \"\"It is just like...\"\" or \"\"It is as if...\"\". まるで (Marude) emphasizes the resemblance. It can be used to modify nouns (～のような), verbs (～のように), or end a sentence (～のようだ).\"",
              "sentences": "このモンスターはとても可愛く、<b>まるで</b>犬<b>のようだ</b>。<br>(This monster is very cute, it's just like a dog.)<br><br>滝<b>のように</b>雨が降る。<br>(The rain falls like a waterfall.)<br><br>この家は<b>まるで</b>人が住んでいない<b>ようだ</b>。<br>(This house looks as if no one is living in it.)<br><br>悪魔<b>のような</b>笑い声。<br>(A laugh like a devil's.)"
